**THIS IS NOT A SUGGESTION. THIS IS A HARD RULE.**

Tobi maintains ALL flash, datalogging, ECU scan, PCAN, V-OP CAN, tune deploy, and related infrastructure code. His code is **production-tested on real ECUs** — meaning it has been verified to correctly flash physical engine control units in real vehicles. **Only Tobi can efficiently fix these files if they break.**

### What happened when this rule was violated:
On **April 9–10, 2026**, AI agent changes to infrastructure files (`server/_core/index.ts`, `loadEnv.ts`, `vite.ts`) and transport files (`pcanConnection.ts`) **broke ECU flashing entirely**. Tobi had to spend an entire morning writing 6 targeted fix commits to repair the damage. This rule exists to **prevent that from EVER happening again**.

